  "hints": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "text": "Think about how you can use the given input to detect a cycle in the linked list."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "text": "Consider using Floyd's cycle-finding algorithm, also known as the \"tortoise and the hare\" algorithm, which uses two pointers moving at different speeds through the list."
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "text": "One pointer should move one step at a time, while the other pointer should move two steps at a time. If there is a cycle, these two pointers will eventually meet."
    },
    {
      "order": 4,
      "text": "To implement this, you can create two variables, one to keep track of the position of the first pointer and one to keep track of the position of the second pointer."
    },
    {
      "order": 5,
      "text": "You can then use these two pointers to traverse the list, checking for a cycle by seeing if they ever meet."
    }
